He may have and probably did kiss her. He probably made some sexist jokes. He's not above reproach. But. But. The picture of him "groping" her was a fucking joke. I am not saying she is a liar. I am saying she is exaggerating and she sat in this until it would benefit the President she voted for

I believe women but there are fucking limits. If my cynicism is actually hypocrisy because of my political leanings, fine. If I am biassed because he is a comedian and he posted for a joke photo, fine. Maybe I am wrong. But I can't help but be more annoyed at Republicans saying "See Democrats? This is what happens when you push your bullshit so safe space politics" than I am at Feanken for his "groping"
Tell me why I am wrong

I'd like someone to tell me why I am wrong because I am having a very difficult time reconciling how I feel about this than other allegations. This feels political, unlike Louis or Bill Cosby or anyone else
To that point this is a single incident vs serial behavior in the others. As a society can we chalk it up to bad taste? I’m genuinely asking to open a conversation about it.
No one wants to hear from white dudes so I am keeping quiet publicly
The kissing part bugs me way more than the picture
Also sucks because Franken is legit one of the best Senators we have
And the right knew we wouldn't hesitate to throw him under the bus

If you believe women you have to believe all women

And if you've ever done any kind of theatre/acting or know women who do, they've all got a story of a guy wanting to "practice"
He probably kissed her which is fucked up. But why exaggerate and say he groped you in your sleep and pretend the picture shows that?
Because the picture is inflammatory, of course.
Yeah, but only because it matches the narrative. "Comedian makes joke in bad taste" isn't a story

I guess this feels different because the Right sees this as a hilarious petard hoist. They don't seem.mad at Franken, they seem relieved nthey can play the "bad people on both sides" card now and defend a pedophile without being called hypocritical

Al Franken once made some shitty choices on a random Tuesday, and that's exactly the same as wanting to elect a bigoted homophobe who likes little girls who we can pass massive corporate tax cuts and take away health care

I think Jason said it best, if you're going to believe women you have to believe all women. Of course Frankenstein "remembers it differently". He's the one being accused. Is it political? No doubt, but what recent accusations Recently hasn't been. I agree it's asinine that the right is trying to use it as justification for their own issues, but that doesn't make either situation any less wrong. If this lady didn't want Franken kissing her it's just the same as any other unwanted advances.
"I remember it differently" is code for "she's fucking lying"
Of course it is..
But he's probably lying, too
He is a politician, y'know..
Fuck everything
He did wrong. We all agree there.
And when all is said and done Franken is probably gonna get fucked Moore is gonna get elected

The picture is whatever, it was a joke in bad taste. I don't really care, but the accusations are there and I don't think we can cherry pick which ones we take seriously and which ones not. Innocent until proven guilty, sure. But that also means you have to take the accusation seriously enough to find the truth

I am upset because we are playing into the Right's hands. I am upset because only one political party is paying the price for doing the right thing. I am upset because net neutrality, health insurance and a 2 trillion dollar tax cut are at stake
It's the same uneven playing field Democrats always have to deal with because they have souls.
At no point would Democrats ever consider making it so people who watch Duck Dynasty can't vote, but making it hard for Democrat voters to get out is a legit GOP strategy
The parties play by entirely different rules.

Well...let's not go that far, <@U4V5EHQ2G>. Dem's sure ain't saints and the Right's being overrun by demagogues and ideologues that they're allowing to shape their party. The Dems are also guilty of inaction and sloth, but that also doesn't matter, because right now we don't have a functioning government of any kind. Instead, we have a kindergarten playground with the bully as class president overseeing it all.
Oh they're absolutely not saints. They're by and large cowardly centrists. But by comparison?
There are absolutely lines Democrats won't cross. That's not the case from the party who elected Donald Trump
This is a weird time in our nation's history. The reconstruction of the Right into a extremist group is their own fault as a reaction to the changing demographics and ideals of America.

They had a choice on how to define conservatism; as a positive force pushing for thoughtful and considered change or the path they took; embracing the most extreme fringes of society and presenting their dogma as traditional American mores and values. The America they appeal to are scared and lost in the changing world around them, so in many ways it's only natural for them to grab the most appealing message that gives them answers and reassures their place in the 'natural order' of things.
I don't know if it was a choice really.

If you open a bar and decorate it entirely with Juggalo merch, play nothing but ICP on the stereo, and make your staff wear clown makeup, you shouldn't be shocked when the only people applying for jobs are Juggalos

It absolutely was; they chose to follow Gingrich and his ilk down this path. Let's face it, Reagan, who was demonized by the Left in the 80s as a demagogue, would be reviled as a liberal sleeper agent by today's Republican party.

The GOP spent a lot of years doing this nudge/wink thing to the worst dregs of society, pretending to be in agreement with them, and suddenly found out that the only people actively running for jobs in the party are people who took them seriously.
They've been taken over by people who weren't in on the scam
They made the scam reality. They were happy to court the votes with empty platitudes, but then Gingrich and others saw that as the only way to shore up their flagging voter base.
Yep
And then the people they were scamming who didn't realize it was a scam started running for office, i.e. the Tea Party
Combine that with Fox News and here we are

Fox News was the same way - they took the most cynical view of their audience to fill the hole for conservative content that wasn't filled by CNN, etc. Unfortunately, their little pantomime became reality and they forgot they were playing a part.
And now Tappedout is randomly changing card versions, whether they are foils, adding autograph notes, etc. So the one reason to keep using that piece of shit site is gone
Yeah it's become so bad it's officially unusable. I've permanently switched to <http://Manastack.com|Manastack.com>. Of all of them, it's the easiest and most efficient at what it does.

I don't give a hot fuck which cards in someone else's deck are foil
I do for my own though if I'm foiling it out
